There are many reasons I'm a fan of Douglas Adams.. first of all, his books are absolutely awesome :) For another thing, he was a huge fan of apple and of macs, never using a pc in his life :) He had a whole family of apple computers, including an Apple II, a macintosh, (ooh yes, the macintosh) and one of the first powerbooks, and has even written articles for such magazines like macuser (some which are published in the The Salmon of Doubt, which was published a little while after his death in May of this year) He complains about dongly things in one of them, and the uselessness of some applications (and also has some fun laughing at pc's during it, even though pc's were never even part of the article) but back to the dongly things.. Douglas Adams, was, of course, British, and had British Apple computers.. So, traveling in the U.S he'd always have to have a universal adaptor, but that's again not part of my point. He complains about the American dongly things on some of his stuff and, oh yeah.. I was gonna have a point to that? Oh yes, that that's one of the things he complains about, that along with Frank the Vandal (Read his books, and then when ur done with all of em, or at least the Dirk Gently and Hitchhiker ones, read The Salmon of Doubt- it's great.. Oh yes, and then rent the 2 dvd set of the television series, or better yet.. buy them! :) ) Anyway, that was basically the point of this entire post :)
